se]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131671980.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/south-korea-court-sentences-ex-president-yoon-to-30-years-in-jail-over-2024-drone-case/articleshow/131671980.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/south-korea-court-sentences-ex-president-yoon-to-30-years-in-jail-over-2024-drone-case/articleshow/131671980.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T08:16:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131672137,imgsize-18270.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Thailand's Princess Bajrakitiyabha dies at 47 after over three years in coma; royal succession in focus]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131671730.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/thailands-princess-bajrakitiyabha-dies-at-47-after-over-three-years-in-coma-royal-succession-in-focus/articleshow/131671730.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/thailands-princess-bajrakitiyabha-dies-at-47-after-over-three-years-in-coma-royal-succession-in-focus/articleshow/131671730.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T07:31:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131671757,imgsize-65914.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[“Free him”: Twitch streamer BruceDropEmOff backs Karmelo Anthony and sparks fierce debate over Austin Metcalf murder conviction]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131671040.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Streamer and YouTuber BruceDropEmOff publicly supported Karmelo Anthony after the teenager was convicted of murdering Austin Metcalf and sentenced to 35 years in prison. Bruce’s “#FREEHIM” message sparked debate online. Supporters viewed it as standing with Anthony, while critics argued it ignored the jury’s decision. The case continues to fuel discussions about race, justice, accountability, and self-defense.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/free-him-twitch-streamer-brucedropemoff-backs-karmelo-anthony-and-sparks-fierce-debate-over-austin-metcalf-murder-conviction/articleshow/131671040.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/free-him-twitch-streamer-brucedropemoff-backs-karmelo-anthony-and-sparks-fierce-debate-over-austin-metcalf-murder-conviction/articleshow/131671040.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T04:55:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131671034,imgsize-634966.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who is Bricks &amp; Minifigs CEO? Ammon McNeff faces tough Coffeezilla questions over missing LEGO Star Wars collection]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131671163.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Coffeezilla’s latest investigation into the Bricks &amp; Minifigs controversy included a direct conversation with CEO Ammon McNeff about a missing LEGO Star Wars collection linked to the Salem, Oregon, store. McNeff said corporate did not know about a spreadsheet tracking the collection. Coffeezilla also revealed documents estimating the collection’s value at roughly $107,000 instead of $200,000.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-bricks-minifigs-ceo-ammon-mcneff-faces-tough-coffeezilla-questions-over-missing-lego-star-wars-collection/articleshow/131671163.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/who-is-bricks-minifigs-ceo-ammon-mcneff-faces-tough-coffeezilla-questions-over-missing-lego-star-wars-collection/articleshow/131671163.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T05:30:34+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131671157,imgsize-543104.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA["If the surgery goes wrong....": Clavicular’s extreme $35,000 jaw surgery plan sparks explosive internet debate over beauty obsession]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131671184.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Streamer Clavicular sparked major online debate after revealing plans for a $35,000 bimaxillary osteotomy, also known as jaw surgery. In a viral interview, he described the painful recovery, cosmetic goals and criticism surrounding the procedure. Social media users were divided, with some praising his honesty while others criticized growing beauty pressures online. The controversy also reignited conversations about appearance culture, influencer fame and the extreme lengths people take for transformation.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/if-the-surgery-goes-wrong-claviculars-extreme-35000-jaw-surgery-plan-sparks-explosive-internet-debate-over-beauty-obsession/articleshow/131671184.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/if-the-surgery-goes-wrong-claviculars-extreme-35000-jaw-surgery-plan-sparks-explosive-internet-debate-over-beauty-obsession/articleshow/131671184.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T05:52:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131671184,imgsize-420604.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Lewis Hamilton’s bold new Barcelona paddock look steals attention while Kim Kardashian exits Europe]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131668736.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Lewis Hamilton drew attention ahead of the Spanish Grand Prix by debuting a new hairstyle in Barcelona. The Ferrari star appeared relaxed and confident after a strong Monaco weekend. His appearance also came shortly after he publicly thanked Kim Kardashian for her support, while reports continue to suggest the couple’s relationship is becoming increasingly serious.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/lewis-hamiltons-bold-new-barcelona-paddock-look-steals-attention-while-kim-kardashian-exits-europe/articleshow/131668736.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/lewis-hamiltons-bold-new-barcelona-paddock-look-steals-attention-while-kim-kardashian-exits-europe/articleshow/131668736.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-12T02:46:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Global Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131668735,imgsize-1384039.cms"/></item></channel></rss>